race.comment: SUNDAY (7) progressed nicely when taken to the front for a gritty second over 1600m at Coonamble in a strong rating race. Best figures measure up and will roll forward again. HARD KNOCK LIFE (4) got off the mark at start ten when a well-deserved maiden winner over 1400m at Taree. Senior rider hops on now and look for her launching late. RHODESIAN DIAMOND (2) gets a much better set-up for this after going back from the draw when a plugging fourth over 1400m at Armidale. Hard fit and senior apprentice takes the reins. MY KIND OF GIRL (6) comes back 200m for this after struggling to see the mile out when sixth over 1600m at Coonamble. Returned good figures when winning at Dubbo two-back. Genuine player. CHARLIE BALI (1) only the one win from twenty starts and recent runs have been sound. Goes into the exotics.
